The paper focuses on a computer vision task of semantic object parsing, which involves understanding the semantic meaning of objects in an image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new neural network architecture called Graph LSTM, which is a generalization of LSTM for graph-structured data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of a confidence-driven scheme for optimization, which involves natural language processing techniques, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of computation and language (cs.CL).
